{
  "texts": [
    "For each of the previous dataset combinations, one BioBERT model and one RoBERTa-ES model were trained.",
    "Continuous training uses a pre-trained system as a starting point for fine-tuning another one, making use of its learnt weights.",
    "First, we fine-tuned the models on the first dataset and using the weights of the trained model as initialiser, we fine-tuned it with the second dataset.",
    "The two base models at the bottom of Table 2 are the starting point for the continuous training with the different datasets.",
    "Six systems were trained: EN + ES, EN Augmented + EN, EN Augmented + ES."
  ]
}